# World Republic Documentation Style Guide

## Capitalization rules

### Headings
- **Main titles (# headings)**: Use title case (e.g., "Mission & Vision", "Legal & Governance")
- **Subheadings (##, ###, ####)**: Use sentence case (e.g., "Mission statement", "Core beliefs", "Democratic participation")

### Bold statements
- **Bold labels in lists**: Use sentence case (e.g., "**User acquisition**:", "**Community growth**:", "**Technical development**:")
- **Bold terms in descriptions**: Use sentence case (e.g., "**Data privacy**: GDPR compliance", "**Political activity**: US regulations")

### Examples of correct usage
✅ **Correct:**
- ## Mission statement
- ### Core beliefs  
- - **User acquisition**: New citizen registrations
- - **Community growth**: Geographic distribution

❌ **Incorrect:**
- ## Mission Statement
- ### Core Beliefs
- - **User Acquisition**: New citizen registrations  
- - **Community Growth**: Geographic distribution

## General writing style
- Use sentence case for all subheadings and bold labels
- Maintain title case only for main document titles (# headings)
- Be consistent across all organizational documentation
